  "prompt": "What is the best kind of frosting for lemon cake?",
  "response": "The best kind of frosting for lemon cake typically depends on personal preference, but some popular choices include:\n\n1. **Lemon Cream Cheese Frosting**: This frosting combines cream cheese's tanginess with fresh lemon juice and zest, providing a rich and flavorful complement to the lemon cake.\n\n2. **Swiss Meringue Buttercream**: This frosting is light and silky, and you can enhance it with lemon zest and juice for a refreshing taste that pairs well with lemon cake.\n\n3. **Buttercream Frosting**: A classic vanilla buttercream can also work well. Adding lemon zest or a bit of lemon extract can enhance the flavor to match the cake.\n\n4. **Lemon Curd**: If you prefer a less sweet option, using lemon curd as a filling or topping can provide a bright and tangy contrast to the cake.\n\n5. **Whipped Cream**: Lightly sweetened whipped cream flavored with lemon can be an elegant and airy choice for lemon cake, particularly in more casual or summer settings.\n\nEach of these frostings will pair nicely with lemon cake, so you can choose based on the texture and flavor you're aiming for!",
